#: ../../V/virtual-Friday.rst:5
msgid "virtual Friday"
msgstr "virtual Friday"

#: ../../V/virtual-Friday.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../V/virtual-Friday.rst:9
msgid ""
"(also logical Friday) The last day before an extended weekend, if that day "
"is not a ‘real’ Friday. For example, the U.S. holiday Thanksgiving is always"
" on a Thursday. The next day is often also a holiday or taken as an extra "
"day off, in which case Wednesday of that week is a virtual Friday (and "
"Thursday is a virtual Saturday, as is Friday). There are also virtual "
"Mondays that are actually Tuesdays, after the three-day weekends associated "
"with many national holidays in the U.S."
msgstr ""
"(logical Fridayとも) "
"長い週末の前の最後の日。ただしその日が‘本当の’金曜日でない場合。たとえば、米国の祝日である感謝祭は常に木曜日である。その翌日もしばしば祝日であるか、または追加の休日とされ、その場合その週の水曜日はvirtual"
" Fridayである(そして木曜日はvirtual "
"Saturdayであり、金曜日もそうである)。また、米国の多くの国民の祝日に伴う三連休の後にある、実際には火曜日であるvirtual "
"Mondayもある。"
